main event: A UFO incident was reported in Roswell, New Mexico on March 6, 1964, and was investigated under Project Blue Book.
interesting points: The report includes multiple black and white photographs of anomalous aerial objects or unidentified flying objects (UFOs) in the night sky.
The photographs depict bright, glowing objects against a dark background, some with streaks or lines around them.
The report appears to be from the Foreign Technology Division of the Air Force Systems Command (AFSC) and is labeled as 'UNCLASSIFIED'.
The report mentions that 12 photographs were taken as part of the incident in Roswell, New Mexico on March 21, 1964.
The report is associated with Project Blue Book, a U.S. Air Force program that investigated unidentified flying objects.
sighted object: bright, glowing objects in the night sky
